Issues.Body:
When i make a async call the template completely freezes and does not update according to the v-if property set. When the async function finishes all the async function the template refreshes again.
`<template>
    <div>
        <p v-if='loading'> loading </p>
        <p v-else> Done </p>
        <button @click="loaddata()">Load data</button>
    </div>
</template>

<script>
export default {
    data(){
        loading: false
    },
    methods: {
        async loaddata() {
            this.loading = true

            // Do async stuff ( encrypt text with openpgp.js )

            this.loading = false
        }
    }
}
</script>`

Expected behavior: Shows loading while it encrypts the text
Behavior: Since it does not updates the template, all the componets get blocked and never shows loading

### Version
2.6.10

### Reproduction link
[https://codepen.io/dreamcarter/pen/ajoePd?editors=1111](https://codepen.io/dreamcarter/pen/ajoePd?editors=1111)







### Steps to reproduce
1. add an array to data like:
    data:{ arr : [1] }
2. binding arr[0] to template: <div>{{ arr[0] }}</div>
3. change arr with index: arr[0] = 2


### What is expected?
we should get <div>2</div>

### What is actually happening?
now we get <div>1</div>,the arr[0] is not responsive

---
In my opinion, we can regard arr as an plain object to make arr[0] = 2 responsive. 

In fact,we know that Object.keys(arr) => ["0"], and it means that arr is an object with a property "0".so if we execute this.walk(arr),arr[0]will be a responsive property now.In this case, we don't need function observeArray.We can make a change in constructor of Observer like this:

src/core/observer/index.js

if (Array.isArray(value)) {

      if (hasProto) {

        protoAugment(value, arrayMethods)

      } else {

        copyAugment(value, arrayMethods, arrayKeys)

      }

      this.observeArray(value)

    } else {

      this.walk(value)

    }

make a change:

if (Array.isArray(value)) {

      if (hasProto) {

        protoAugment(value, arrayMethods)

      } else {

        copyAugment(value, arrayMethods, arrayKeys)

      }

}

this.walk(value)

In this time,we regard arr = [1] as arr = { "0": 1 }.So, we don't need observeArray in the constructor of Observer and make all initial items of arr responsive.But if arr[0] doesn't exist initially, it is not responsive because it's a new property for arr.

